# Patterns for skills/file-folder-name-linter/ to skip.
# One glob per line. Lines starting with # are comments.
# Patterns match against repo-relative POSIX paths. Use `*` for one path
# segment, `**` to span multiple segments, and a trailing `/` to scope a
# pattern to a directory.

# Vendored skills, dotfiles, and standard repo docs (README.md, AGENTS.md,
# MEMORY.md, ONBOARDING.md, LICENSE, ...) are already ignored by default.
# Add only project-specific exceptions below.

# notes/ branch-salvage companion artifacts: genuine code, config, diff, and
# data files (.vue/.css/.patch/.tsv) preserved verbatim from deleted branches.
# Their extensions fall outside the notes/ allowed set (md and image only), so
# they can never satisfy the date-prefixed-markdown rule; their names are kept
# as their original upstream identities and are referenced as-is from the notes.
notes/**/*.vue
notes/**/*.css
notes/**/*.patch
notes/**/*.tsv
